{"word":"G1199 - δεσμόν - desmón - des-mon' - Band","slug":"G1199","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">δεσμόν</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>desmón"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>des-mon'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Band"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B4;&#x03B5;&#x03C3;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03BD;, &#x03B4;&#x03B5;&#x03C3;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03C2; - desmon  desmos</b> - <i>des-mon', des-mos'</i><p/>Neuter and masculine respectively from <a href=\"#/G1210\">G1210</a>; a <i>band</i>, that is, <i>ligament</i> (of the body) or <i>shackle</i> (of a prisoner); figuratively an <i>impediment</i> or <i>disability:</i> - band, bond, chain, string."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1198\">G1198</a>"}]}